@startuml User_Journey_Map

!theme plain

skinparam linetype ortho
skinparam packageStyle rectangle

title WhatsChat User Journey Map

' ============================================
' Journey stages
' ============================================

package "Discovery" #E3F2FD {
  class Discovery {
    + Learn about product
    + Visit website
    + View feature overview
    --
    User actions:
    - Discover via search/recommendation
    - Visit site to learn features
    - Watch demo or screenshots
    --
    Emotion: 😊 Curious, expectant
    Pain points:
    - Unclear information
    - Lack of live demo
    Opportunities:
    - Product demos
    - SEO improvement
  }
}

package "Registration" #BBDEFB {
  class Registration {
    + Create account
    + Verify email
    + Complete profile
    --
    User actions:
    - Fill form (name, email, phone, password)
    - Receive verification email
    - Set avatar and status
    --
    Emotion: 😐 Cautious, patient
    Pain points:
    - Long signup flow
    - Email verification delay
    - Unclear password rules
    Opportunities:
    - Simplify signup
    - Social login
    - Password strength hint
  }
}

package "First Use" #90CAF9 {
  class FirstUse {
    + Log in
    + Explore UI
    + Add contacts
    --
    User actions:
    - Log in with email/password
    - Browse main UI (chats, status, calls)
    - Search and add first contact
    - Send first message
    --
    Emotion: 😊 Excited, exploring
    Pain points:
    - Many features to learn
    - Empty contact list
    - Unclear how to start
    Opportunities:
    - Onboarding
    - People you may know
    - Sample conversation
  }
}

package "Daily Use" #64B5F6 {
  class DailyUse {
    + Send messages
    + Receive messages
    + View status
    --
    User actions:
    - Send text, image, voice
    - Receive and reply
    - View contact status
    - Search history
    - Manage chat list
    --
    Emotion: 😊 Satisfied, habitual
    Pain points:
    - Send failures
    - Network delay
    - Hard to find history
    Opportunities:
    - Sync improvement
    - Better search
    - Message backup
  }
}

package "Advanced Features" #42A5F5 {
  class AdvancedFeatures {
    + Voice/video calls
    + Group chat
    + File sharing
    --
    User actions:
    - Start voice/video call
    - Create or join group
    - Share file, location, contact
    - Manage group members
    --
    Emotion: 😊 Satisfied, efficient
    Pain points:
    - Unstable call quality
    - Complex group management
    - File size limits
    Opportunities:
    - WebRTC tuning
    - Simpler group actions
    - Large file support
  }
}

package "Maintenance" #1E88E5 {
  class Maintenance {
    + Settings
    + Privacy
    + Data management
    --
    User actions:
    - Update profile and avatar
    - Privacy (last seen, avatar visibility)
    - Notification settings
    - Clear chats and media
    - Change password
    --
    Emotion: 😐 Rational, cautious
    Pain points:
    - Scattered settings
    - Inflexible privacy
    - Awkward data cleanup
    Opportunities:
    - Single settings entry
    - Finer privacy controls
    - Bulk actions
  }
}

' ============================================
' Journey flow
' ============================================

Discovery --> Registration : Decides to sign up
Registration --> FirstUse : Signup success
FirstUse --> DailyUse : Familiar with basics
DailyUse --> AdvancedFeatures : Explores advanced
AdvancedFeatures --> Maintenance : Needs personalisation
Maintenance --> DailyUse : Back to daily use

' ============================================
' Emotion curve
' ============================================

note right of Discovery
  **Emotion: Curious → Expectant**
  
  User is curious about the product
  and expects it to meet comms needs
end note

note right of Registration
  **Emotion: Cautious → Patient**
  
  Signup requires input;
  user may find it tedious but completes
end note

note right of FirstUse
  **Emotion: Excited → Exploring**
  
  First time with new features,
  user is eager to explore
end note

note right of DailyUse
  **Emotion: Satisfied → Habitual**
  
  Daily use becomes routine,
  satisfaction is high
end note

note right of AdvancedFeatures
  **Emotion: Satisfied → Efficient**
  
  Advanced features boost efficiency,
  satisfaction increases
end note

note right of Maintenance
  **Emotion: Rational → Cautious**
  
  User manages account and data
  with focus on privacy and security
end note

' ============================================
' Touchpoints
' ============================================

package "Touchpoints" #FFF9C4 {
  class Touchpoints {
    + Site / login page
    + Signup form
    + Main UI
    + Chat UI
    + Call UI
    + Settings page
    --
    Each touchpoint is
    a key moment for UX
  }
}

Discovery ..> Touchpoints : Site visit
Registration ..> Touchpoints : Signup form
FirstUse ..> Touchpoints : Main UI
DailyUse ..> Touchpoints : Chat UI
AdvancedFeatures ..> Touchpoints : Call UI
Maintenance ..> Touchpoints : Settings

' ============================================
' Opportunities summary
' ============================================

legend right
  |<#E3F2FD> Discovery | Demos, SEO |
  |<#BBDEFB> Registration | Simplify flow, social login |
  |<#90CAF9> First Use | Onboarding, suggest contacts |
  |<#64B5F6> Daily Use | Sync, search |
  |<#42A5F5> Advanced | Performance, simpler actions |
  |<#1E88E5> Maintenance | Single entry, finer controls |
  |
  |😊 Positive | Satisfied, excited |
  |😐 Neutral | Rational, cautious |
  |😞 Negative | Issues, friction |
endlegend

@enduml
